TITLE: Jumping Horizontal Offset on Arrow Key Press in ScrollView (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to jump the horizontal offset of a ScrollView by specific values when processing Left and Right Arrow keystrokes. It uses the ScrollBy method with disabled animation for a FlipView-like experience.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/microsoft-ui-xaml/blob/main/specs/ScrollingControls/ScrollView.md#2025-04-16_snippet_29

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
protected override void OnKeyUp(KeyRoutedEventArgs e)
{
    base.OnKeyUp(e);
    if (e.Key == VirtualKey.Left)
    {
        _scrollView.ScrollBy(
            horizontalOffsetDelta: -_previousGroup.Width,
            verticalOffsetDelta: 0.0,
            new ScrollingScrollOptions(ScrollingAnimationMode.Disabled));
    }
    else if (e.Key == VirtualKey.Right)
    {
        _scrollView.ScrollBy(
            horizontalOffsetDelta: _currentGroup.Width,
